Let me know if anything else looks stale or needs updating based on your review of the files.

Key architecture notes to know before touching anything:

RACE_GROUP is built dynamically in rebuildRaceGroup() after every standings load — do not hardcode it
remaining() uses ST[team].gp (games played from standings) to slice the schedule — completed games drop off automatically
tbEdge() is purely tiebreaker-based (RW → ROW → W), ignoring pts — do not change this
posProb() has a hard 0% mathematical elimination floor — preserve this
The race table threshold is Math.min(nyiGl + 2, 4) — keeps the field tight late in the season
All Metro #3 and WC2 target teams are derived from live standings — nothing is hardcoded to PHI or OTT

The NEXT_SEASON_SETUP.md file in the repo has detailed documentation of everything, including lessons learned from the 2025-26 season. Please read it before making any changes.

